@startuml battery_soc_to_bms_pack_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Battery SOC To BMS Pack State Signal Flow\n(energy input -> BAT_BMS -> CPC / observers)

actor "Energy source\nbattery / charge input" as Energy #F4F7FB
participant "Input context\nbatterySoc + chargingState" as Inp #E8F0FE
participant "BAT_BMS\nbattery pack owner" as BMS #E8F7E8
participant "CPC\npower consumer" as CPC #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / tests" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Pack-State Inputs ==

Energy -> Inp : battery SOC / charging status update
Inp -> BMS : gBatterySoc\ngChargingState
activate BMS
BMS -> BMS : apply stale-input fallback\nwhen source age is broken
BMS -> BMS : derive BmsState
BMS -> BMS : map PackSoc directly
BMS -> BMS : derive PackTemp from SOC / charge state
note right of BMS
Representative inputs
- batterySoc
- chargingState

Representative outputs
- BmsState
- PackSoc
- PackTemp
end note

== Pack-State Publish ==

BMS -> CPC : frmBatBmsStateMsg
BMS -> Obs : BAT_BMS trace / observer view
note right of CPC
Representative consumer
- CPC uses BmsState / PackSoc / PackTemp
  for energy and downstream power context
end note
deactivate BMS

note over Energy, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Battery SOC and charging state reach BAT_BMS
2. BAT_BMS normalizes stale cases and derives pack state
3. frmBatBmsStateMsg is published to CPC
4. Tests and observers verify pack-state transitions
end note

@enduml
